 Port Elizabeth - A 26-year-old suspect is expected in court after he was arrested just two hours after a shooting incident occurred in Glendenning Street in Shauderville, Port Elizabeth, on Friday. "It is alleged that on Friday, at about 19:45, the 21-year-old complainant was standing outside the shop in Glendenning Street with his friends when he saw the suspect walking towards him," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "The suspect pointed a firearm towards them and fired several shots in their direction. "The suspect then fled the scene on foot." Col Naidu said that the suspect is known to the complainant and at about 22:00, the Anti-Gang Unit members arrested the suspect, who was found sitting in a car nearby. "He was arrested and detained on a charge of attempted murder and is expected to appear in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate's Court on Monday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  